<H3> <TI>   MDN Calls for Antiembargo Demonstration 4 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0402002794 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0402002794 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A demonstration is scheduled for 4 February. 
Mobilization for National Development [MDN] plans to demonstrate 
against the embargo and in favor of the employers' movement. 
Professor DeRonceray, a fierce opponent of Father Aristide, 
asserts that the embargo has only undermined our economy and 
worsened the misery of the poor. It is urgent that he go down to 
the streets to say no to the embargo. The demonstration, which 
will begin in Colomb Quay, will stop in front of the parliament 
and the U.S. Embassy. Let us listen to Hubert De Ronceray. 
  [Begin recording, in Creole] Through this demonstration we 
will join with the businessmen, will say no to the embargo 
imposed on the people by the international community, and will 
say yes to a solution coming from inside the country. MDN 
invites all its partisans and friends in Port-au-Prince to 
participate in this demonstration, and all people living in the 
provinces and the rural sections to organize peaceful marches to 
force the deputies and senators to be done with the Aristide 
matter and to implement Article 149 of the Constitution. We will 
then have a provisional government of concord that will unblock 
the country, and will hold elections for the installation of a 
definitive government. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

