<H3> <TI>   Striker's Accept Conditions </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0402012394 Guatemala City Teleonce Television in Spanish 
1900 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0402012394 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Teleonce Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Telepress" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The government and the National Transportation 
Coordinating Board reached an agreement early today, thus fuel 
supplies are expected to return to normal in the next few hours 
and suburban transportation to resume. 
  President Ramiro De Leon Carpio confirmed that the 
transportation workers accepted the conditions proposed by the 
government. 
  [Begin De Leon recording] Yesterday they accepted the 
government economic policy proposed by the president. The only 
[words indistinct] is that today we will issue the respective 
agreements, but they accepted the economic policy. The CNT 
accepted the proposals and tariffs we presented, so we are 
satisfied because the problem has been resolved. There will be 
no strike. At this time today they must inform their members 
and transportation workers that the problem has been resolved. 
This is one less problem for the country. We are extremely 
pleased to see that the government's firm position was accepted, 
as the government's position must be and will be accepted when 
we are facing problems that require state decisions. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

