  [Editorial Report] Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 
on 27 January 94, page 105 reports that official sources 
disclosed that on 26 January the Inter-American Development Bank 
(IDB) granted $132 million in credit to the Guatemalan 
Government to improve solvency of the financial system and 
increase access to credit. Edmond Mulet, Guatemalan ambassador 
to the United States, and IDB President Enrique Iglesias signed 
the agreement. 

