<H3> <TI>   * Budget for 1994 Tops 6.1 Billion Lempiras </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94CA0060A Tegucigalpa EL HERALDO in Spanish 16 Dec 93 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> 94CA0060A </F>
<F P=104>  Tegucigalpa EL HERALDO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] The General Budget of Revenues and Expenditures of 
the Republic for fiscal year 1994 will total 6,183,096,752 
lempiras, according to the report on the matter that was the 
subject of an initial debate in the National Congress yesterday. 
  Of that total, 67,094,494 lempiras is budgeted for the 
legislative branch, 65,551,100 for the judicial branch, and 
6,024,951,158 for the executive branch. 
  In addition, the Electoral Body (National Tribunal of 
Elections) will receive 25.5 million lempiras, while the 
Presidency of the Republic will be allocated 23,961,805 lempiras. 
  The executive branch budget can be broken down as follows: 


------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
