<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Repudiates U.S. Human Rights Report </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0202222394 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2100 GMT 2 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0202222394 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Brazilian Government has repudiated, through 
Brazilian newspapers, the annual report on human rights issued 
by the U.S. State Department. The U.S. report released 
yesterday included Brazil among the countries that violate 
civilian rights. 
  In its reaction to the U.S. report, the Brazilian Government 
considers as unfounded charges of disrespect for civilian rights 
because the document does not consider the efforts by the 
Brazilian federal, state, and municipal governments to solve the 
problem. 
  The Brazilian Government believes the subject must be 
discussed by international organizations and stresses that the 
accusation is unacceptable because the U.S. Government does not 
release reports on human rights violations in its own territory. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

