<H3> <TI>   * PL Holds Overwhelming Congressional Majority </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94CA0060E San Pedro Sula TIEMPO in Spanish 30 Nov 93 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> 94CA0060E </F>
<F P=104>  San Pedro Sula TIEMPO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Text] Tegucigalpa--The Liberal Party (PL) will be entitled 
to 71 deputy seats, the National Party (PN) 55 seats, and the 
Innovation and Unity Party (PINU) two seats, according to the 
calculations of Radio America, whose modern methods have proven 
to be the most efficient. 
  The parties' relative positions in Congress were reversed, 
since the National Party has 71 seats in the current session, 
the Liberals 55, and the PINU two, while the Christian Democrats 
still have no seats at all. 

