<F P=100> Bolivia </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Police Commander Installed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0502165294 La Paz Television Nacional Network in Spanish 
0100 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0502165294 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Television Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] At 1800 this afternoon President Gonzalo Sanchez 
de Lozada installed recently promoted General Luis Rocha 
Martinez as the new commander of the Bolivian police. 
  Before installing the new police commander, the president 
praised the work done by the deposed General Einar Lopez: 
  [Begin Sanchez recording] We must outline the important 
contribution made by Gen. Lopez, who is leaving this post, not 
only because of his absolutely honest performance, but also 
because of his dedication to the institution, his service to the 
community, and his important contribution to the beginning of a 
process, a plan, a project to reorganize the institution. [end 
recording] 
  The president said the country will need the services of 
Gen. 
Lopez when analyzing the measures necessary to bring the police 
closer to the people. 
  Gen. Einar Lopez was not present during the ceremony at 
government palace. The president also said that Gen. Rocha 
Martinez, the new police commander, was a man of unblemished 
honesty. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

