<F P=102>  FL0402224394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0402224394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Carlos Lage, vice president of the Council of State, 
will meet today in Brasilia with President Itamar Franco as part 
of his official visit to Brazil. The trip will conclude on 7 
February. 
  On 3 February, Lage meet with Foreign Minister Celso Amorim 
and other personalities of the Brazilian Government. Lage's 
visit is receiving extensive media coverage, particularly by 
Rio's O GLOBO which featured an interview, with written 
responses to questions submitted before the trip, in which Lage 
discusses various issues, including Cuba's economic situation. 
  It was also announced that in an interview by AGENCIA BRASIL 
Lage pointed out that the U.S. blockade against Cuba has caused 
many difficulties and added that it is essential that Latin 
America reject this form of aggression. 
  A PRENSA LATINA dispatch adds that during his meeting with 
Lage, the Brazilian foreign minister criticized the U.S. 
blockade against Cuba by rejecting unilateral measures by 
certain countries in violation of international law. 

</TEXT>

