<F P=102>  PA0502192394 Havana Radio Havana Cuba in Spanish 1300 GMT 5 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0502192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Havana Cuba </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Morning Information Review" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Carlos Lage, vice president of the Cuban Council of 
State [as heard], arrived today in Rio de Janeiro as part of the 
last stage of his official visit to Brazil. Shortly after 
arriving, Lage met with Rio de Janeiro business representatives. 
  During a news conference that took place shortly before 
leaving Brasilia, the Cuban vice president described talks with 
Brazilian President Itamar Franco, Foreign Minister Celso 
Amorim, Finance Minister Fernando Henrique Cardoso, and Health 
Minister Henrique Santillo as positive. 
  Lage remarked that during the interview with President 
Franco 
they discussed issues related to enhancing political and 
economic relations between Cuba and Brazil. He highlighted that 
the Brazilian president reiterated his criticisms of the U.S. 
blockade against Cuba and the so-called Torricelli Bill just as 
Foreign Minister Amorim had done. 
  The Cuban vice president explained that his country offers 
opportunities for foreign investments especially in the tourism 
sector. He also pointed out that businessmen who decide to 
invest in Cuba will be able to recover it in a short period of 
time. 

</TEXT>

