<H3> <TI>   Medical Technology Exchange Agreement Signed With Peru </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0402224294 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2030 GMT 
4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0402224294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Important agreements have been signed in Peru 
between Cuba and Peruvian institutions. These agreements between 
Cuba and the social security institutes from Lima and Arequipa 
include the exchange of technology, professionals, and patients. 
  Professor Rodrigo Alvarez Cambras, director of the Cuban 
Orthopedics Hospital, said that he is visiting Peru at the 
invitation of the Peruvian Social Security Institute, and that 
for two weeks he toured several important towns. 
  Accompanied by Dr. (Luis Fleitas), a Peruvian expert, 
Alvarez 
Cambras conducted several surgeries and gave seven outstanding 
lectures on external pin fixation, pseudarthrosis surgery, 
ligaments, and bone diseases. 
  Alvarez Cambras said that technological and professional 
exchange will also take place between the two countries, in view 
of the fact that the two countries expressed great interest in 
this field. 

