a country where human rights are not protected and where the 
criminals who staged the coup d'etat are using violence. This is 
why we in the Fort St. Clair group say first that the United 
States should stop stalling for time while speaking of the 
Governors Island and the New York pacts. We unreservedly support 
a demonstration to be held on 6 and 7 February by the masses and 
all worthy military so democracy can be established in Haiti 
with President Jean-Bertrand Aristide in power. [end recording] 

