<F P=100> Dominican Republic </F>
<F P=101> Haiti </F>
<H3> <TI>   Christian Democrat Leader Opposed to Demonstrations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0502145694 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0502145694 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Christian Democratic Assembly [RDC] leader Eddy 
Volel opposes the demonstration scheduled for 4 February. 
According to Volel, some sectors have the right to demonstrate 
in the streets whereas others do not. 
  [Begin Volel recording, in Creole] There is a sector that is 
struggling for democracy, but that does not have the right to 
speak, even less does it have the right to stage demonstrations 
or to hold meetings. We in the RDC are always against this 
stance that favors a person or a group of persons to the 
detriment of another person or group of persons. We could never 
offer our support, we never offered our support, and we will 
never offer our support to anything done against the interests 
of the people. So, we do not offer our support: We oppose this 
demonstration. We are against this disorder because those 
people, who are staging the demonstration, have never done 
anything for the Haitian people. On the contrary, they have 
always tried to destroy the people, to destroy the country. [end 
rcording] 

</TEXT>

