<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Development Secretary, Chiapas Governor Sign Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0402165894 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0402165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 3 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Social Development Secretary Carlos Rojas Gutierrez 
and Chiapas State Governor Javier Lopez Moreno have signed the 
1994 social development agreement. The document establishes 
that 750 million new pesos will be assigned to the development 
of social projects in that state. 
  During the ceremony, the social development secretary said 
that the public projects and investments that have been carried 
out are not enough because the situation in the state is the 
product of centuries of backwardness. This is why it is 
necessary to respect the decisions of the community and to 
listen to and heed their proposals and their truth, he said. 
  Javier Lopez Moreno said that efforts to integrate a 
political coalition government will continue because this is 
what the current situation demands. 
  At the end of the ceremony, the officials went to Comitan, 
Chiapas, where they inaugurated one of the 16 health centers 
that will function in the state for peasants and Indians. 

</TEXT>

