<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   FSE Vote Delayed Again `for Lack of Quorum' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0402142994 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 0900 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0402142994 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Cristina Indio do Brasil] </F>
  [Text] Voting on the Social Emergency Fund [FSE] has been 
postponed until 7 February. During the final congressional 
session of the week, congressmen approved just one amendment; 
which grants more power to legislators. 
  Congress will probably vote on the amendment that creates 
the 
FSE on 7 February. Yesterday congressmen approved a proposal to 
invert the agenda and vote on this amendment before others. For 
lack of quorum, however, everything was postponed until next 
week. Only an amendment that grants more power to Congress was 
approved yesterday. As a result of this amendment, congressmen 
can now summon for questioning by the Congressional 
Investigation Committees not only ministers but also 
second-echelon officials and directors of state-owned companies. 

</TEXT>

