<H3> <TI>   Cardoso To Resign If Fund Not Approved </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0402140694 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 0900 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0402140694 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Leaders of the Brazilian Social Democracy Party, 
Mario Covas and Jose Serra, support the finance minister's 
decision to resign if Congress does not approve the 
establishment of the FSE. 
  Senator Pedro Simon, government leader at Congress, has 
confirmed that Minister Fernando Henrique Cardoso will leave his 
position if the FSE is not approved. Cardoso said if his 
presence at the ministry is creating difficulties, he will leave. 

</TEXT>

