<H3> <TI>   First TSE Report Shows Figueres Leading </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0702032794 Paris AFP in Spanish 0250 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0702032794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] San Jose, 6 Feb (AFP) -- According to the first 
report issued by the Supreme Electoral Tribunal (TSE), social 
democratic candidate Jose Maria Figueres leads the presidential 
election held today with 51.38 percent of the votes compared to 
46.11 percent for his ruling party adversary Miguel Angel 
Rodriguez. 
  In the first official count of 191,727 votes from 1,111 
polling tables out of a total of 8,363 tables throughout the 
country, Figueres, of the National Liberation Party (PLN) 
received 98,506 votes, while Rodriguez, of the Social Christian 
Unity (PUSC), got 88,406 votes. 
  Approximately 1.9 million Costa Ricans were eligible today 
to 
vote for a new president, two vice presidents, 87 congressional 
deputies, and municipal authorities for the country's cantons. 

</TEXT>

