<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Opposes Formation of Truth Commission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0602160394 Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 3 Feb 94 
p 2 </F>

<F P=103> PA0602160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] For the first time ever, Defense Minister General 
Mario Rene Enriquez Morales admitted yesterday that the Army has 
always opposed the establishment of a Truth Commission because 
it considers that such a commission would be used for actions of 
revenge instead of to reconcile the Guatemalan people. 
  Enriquez Morales, who participated in the Peace Commission 
for two years, said the talks have always had this objective as 
their sole purpose and that the Truth Commission, which he 
called "the vengeance commission," would only polarize society 
further. 
  He added: The formation of this commission has always been 
opposed, and I will tell you why. We object to it because it 
will attempt to open the wounds of events that occurred in 1980, 
1981, and 1982, and this would not help the country at all but, 
quite the contrary, would promote confrontation. 
  The defense minister concluded: We would accept the 
formation 
of a commission, but of real truth and not the one you formed 
because, in this case, the actions are aimed against the Army 
and the government in general, because the clandestine guerrilla 
would not be identifiable. [sentence as published] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

