<F P=100> Honduras </F>
<H3> <TI>   Journalists Association Calls For Boycott Against Reina </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0502130794 Tegucigalpa EL PERIODICO DE HONDURAS in Spanish 
4 Feb 94 p 37 </F>

<F P=103> PA0502130794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tegucigalpa EL PERIODICO DE HONDURAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tegucigalpa -- The Honduran Journalists Association 
(CPH) yesterday ordered accredited professional journalists to 
abandon the Presidency as a new way to show President Reina that 
they deserve respect. 
  This resolution, which EL PERIODICO DE HONDURAS will honor 
and support, is a result of the very bad treatment journalists 
have received not only from [Presidential Private Secretary] 
Lucio Izaguirre, but also from President Reina, who labeled us 
as "money changers." The following is the official communique 
issued by the CPH Board of Directors. 
<H5>  Communique No. 1 </H5>
  The CPH Board of Directors orders all affiliates, members, 
and licensed students who cover the Presidency to immediately 
cease all news coverage related to Presidential House activities. 
  This measure will be in effect until the corresponding 
authorities negotiate with the CPH to allow journalists who 
cover the Presidential House to return within a framework of 
dignity and responsibility. The problem will not be solved in 
an atmosphere of luncheons and dinners as has been irresponsibly 
suggested. 
  [Signed] The Board of Directors 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

