<F P=100> Dominican Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Presidential Candidate Escapes Assassination Attempt </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0502201294 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1845 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0502201294 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Santo Domingo, 5 Feb (EFE) -- Jose Pena Gomez, the 
presidential candidate of the social democratic Dominican 
Revolutionary Party [PRD], escaped without injuries Friday night 
from an attack, during which a person accompanying him, Melania 
Lora, received a bullet wound in her left leg. 
  Lora, the leader of the Education Department of the 
Federation of Social Democratic Women, explained today at the 
hospital where she was admitted that the attack took place when 
Pena Gomez, senate candidate Milagros Ortiz Bosch, and she were 
participating in a march in Maquiteria, a densely populated east 
Santo Domingo neighborhood. She explained that the three had 
been in a vehicle. When they stepped out to initiate a walk in 
favor of the PRD, rocks were thrown at them from the roof of a 
nearby building and shots were heard. 
  Lora affirmed that she was wounded because she was beside 
the 
presidential candidate and that the attack was directed against 
him. 

</TEXT>

