<H3> <TI>   Attorney General Wants Armed Peasant Group Investigated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0402211394 Asuncion HOY in Spanish 4 Feb 94 p 59 </F>
<F P=103> PY0402211394 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion HOY </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Attorney General Luis Emilio Escobar Faella has 
asked the San Pedro de Ycuamandiyu trial judge to investigate a 
group of peasants from Tava'i Borda who are allegedly involved 
in guerrilla activities in the area. The attorney general has 
lodged a formal protest before the court against the peasants on 
charges of illegal association for criminal purposes, and for 
perpetrating crimes against persons and the security of the 
state. [passage omitted] 
  The report adds that in the Tava'i Borda II area, groups of 
peasants are allegedly armed with guns, including submachine 
guns. 
  The alleged leaders of the guerrilla group have been 
identified as Elvio Benitez and Venancio Zeballos. They 
reportedly persecute those who disagree with them and 
indoctrinating the rest to engage in unlawful practices in the 
area, such as stealing cattle and the illegal lumber trade. 
[passage omitted] 

