<H3> <TI>   Coffee Growers Dissatisfied </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0702005594 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1730 GMT 4 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0702005594 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Despite the much-awaited coffee price increase, 
coffee growers are not satisfied and insist that the 120,000 
pesos [unit not given] do not even cover production costs. 
  [Begin recording] [Coffee grower Alfonso Lopez] I see this 
as 
something wicked by the government, because it is a well-known 
fact that this price will never cover costs. 
  [Coffee grower Jairo Barragan] The price the government has 
just set is not what we coffee growers expected. We are 
demanding a 30 percent increase to make this profitable. 
  [Coffee grower Manuel Hernandez] It does not make up for the 
costs involved, especially when you take into account the stalk 
borer plague. 
  [Coffee grower Aurelio Suarez] The truth is that this 
government was unable to resolve the coffee problem. 
  [Unidentified reporter] What are you going to do now? 
  [Coffee grower Jose Acosta] Go hungry. What use is this 
increase? 
  [Coffee grower Enrique Angel Mejia] We are disenchanted and 
worried about the new coffee prices because to balance out 
production costs and income the increase should have been at 
least double. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

