<H3> <TI>   Ambassador, Legislators Travel to U.S. for Consultation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0702182194 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1145 
GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0702182194 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A delegation of Haitian legislators is visiting the 
United States for high-level consultations. The Haitian 
legislators, including Firmin Jean-Louis and Frantz Robert 
Monde, are scheduled to meet with officials of the U.S. State 
Department and, possibly, with President-in-Exile Jean-Bertrand 
Aristide. Minister of National Education Victor Benoit, U.S. 
Ambassador William Lacy Swing, and Dante Caputo's political 
adviser, Leandro Despouilles, are with the delegation. Haitian 
legislative delegates include Senator Julio Larosiliere; the 
president of the Chamber of Deputies, Deputy Frantz Robert 
Monde; and Deputies Jean Talendier [Desjardins] and Jean-Jacques 
Seignon. 

