<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Main Parties Register Candidates; Alliances `Frustrated' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0702235594 Panama City Circuito RPC Television in Spanish 
2300 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0702235594 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Circuito RPC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "RPC Television News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The main political parties today officially 
registered their respective presidential candidates for the 
elections to be held in May. 
  The first party to do so was the PRD [Democratic 
Revolutionary Party], then the Papa Egoro Movement, the 
Arnulfist Party and the Liberal Party, and finally the Morena 
[National Renewal Movement], Molirena [Nationalist Liberal 
Republican Movement], and Civic Renewal Party. 
  With the registration of the candidates headed by Mireya 
Moscoso de Gruber on the one hand, and Ruben Dario Carles on the 
other, the possibility of an alliance that would group the civic 
[civilistas] forces that struggled against Manuel Antonio 
Noriega's regime has been frustrated. With these four [number 
as heard] slates the political panorama is clarified and the 
uncertainty about the presidential candidacies disappears. 
  Now, only the Solidarity Party and the Democratic Christian 
Party have yet to register their candidates. Last week, Jose 
Salvador Munoz registered as presidential candidate for the 
Doctrinaire Panamenist Party. 
  In accordance with the electoral scheme, there are seven 
candidates for president of the Republic in the first free and 
democratic elections to be held after over 20 years of military 
dictatorships. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

