<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Mexican Government today regretted that a U.S. 
jury returned a verdict of not guilty in the case of a policeman 
charged with killing a Mexican in Phoenix, Arizona. The Mexican 
Foreign Relations Secretariat said this could set a precedent of 
impunity for those who murder Mexican citizens. 

