<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Good Morning From Mexico" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Two PRI [Institutional Revolutionary Party] rival 
groups that are disputing municipal headship in San Mateo, 
Atengo, Mexico State, clashed on the morning of 3 February, 
causing severe damage to municipal headquarters and injury to 
several individuals. One municipal police patrol vehicle and a 
private vehicle were torched during the clashes. Both sides are 
fighting over the San Mateo Municipality, Atengo, one in favor 
of Santiago Cepeda and the other in favor of (Gustavo Sejuro). 

