  [Text] Lima, 7 Feb (AFP) -- According to eyewitnesses, at 
least one person was killed and several injured this morning 
when a high intensity bomb exploded at the Peruvian Air Force 
headquarters in downtown Lima. According to area residents, the 
explosion, which took place at 0645, caused serious damage. 
  After half an hour no official confirmation had yet been 
announced. 

