<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Political Party Offices Bombed in Santander </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0702155594 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1509 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0702155594 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bucaramanga (Colombia), 7 Feb (EFE) -- Three people 
were injured today in one of four bomb attacks against four 
political party offices in cities in Colombia's Santander 
Department (in the northeast part of the country), including the 
department's capital of Bucaramanga, according to authorities. 
  Police report the explosive devices were activated by urban 
commando units of communist guerrillas from the National 
Liberation Army (ELN), which operates in Bucaramanga and the 
nearby towns of Giron, Floridablanca, and Piedecuesta. 
According to one source, three people in Giron were treated at 
a hospital for minor injuries they incurred in one of the blasts. 
  The offices that were attacked belonged to Aquiles Tores 
Breton, candidate for mayor of Bucaramanga; conservative 
candidate Jorge Humberto Mantilla; a civic movement in Giron; 
and Consuelo Duran de Mustafa in Piedecuesta. In December, 
other Santander political party offices belonging to candidates 
running in the 13 March congressional and municipal elections 
were also targets of similar bomb attacks in actions attributed 
to the ELN guerrillas. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

