Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

  [Excerpt] The president of the House of Representatives 
Second Commission, Lucas Lebolo Conde, denounced the use of 
large sums of money in the political campaigns in various 
municipalities of Atlantico and he said the Treasury Inspector 
should conduct an investigation. 
  The situation is so worrisome, judging from what other 
politicians have said, that some of them have decided to unite 
in a common front to defend their political territory because 
the money is coming from persons in other departments or outside 
the country. 
  He also asked Treasury Inspector Jorge Garcia and Prosecutor 
General Gustavo de Greiff to investigate the source of financing 
of the different candidates for Congress since "the fortunes 
spent in this department in the months of November and December 
are not in conformity with the stipulated legal standards for 
investing in campaigns." [passage omitted] 

