<H3> <TI>   Court President Terms `Irresponsible' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0802200394 San Salvador Radio Cadena YSU in Spanish 1800 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0802200394 </F>
<F P=104>  San Salvador Radio Cadena YSU </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "YSU Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] In another turn of events, 
Supreme Court President Mauricio Gutierrez Castro has termed as 
irresponsible the report presented to the United Nations by 
human rights expert (name indistinct). The human rights expert 
on 24 January presented a report to the United Nations in which 
he stated individual rights are still being violated in El 
Salvador. Here is what Gutierrez Castro has said: 
  [Begin Gutierrez Castro recording, in progress] ...report. 
First, I am not surprised, as many of these individuals hold 
their posts by issuing alarming reports. If you are appointed 
to watch over something and you report that everything is 
alright, then why do they need you? Second, I think it is 
irresponsible on the part of a person who has not even come 
here--he has not visited the courts, has no knowledge of the 
process, has not seen any of this-- to issue reports criticizing 
or labeling the human rights situation here. 
  For example, you are giving an account of what is being said 
here. How can you give an account? You can give an account 
because you are present, you are hearing what is going on, you 
are perceiving it through the [words indistinct]. I do not 
think you could be giving a report on what is being done at the 
Legal Medical Institute if you were in New York; therefore it is 
absurd. I think it is irresponsible to issue such a report. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

