<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arrest of Alpha 66 Members by U.S. Coast Guard Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL0802170194 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0802170194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The U.S. Coast Guard arrested members of the 
anti-Cuban terrorist organization Alpha 66, who were traveling 
on board a boat on which agents found weapons, ammunition, and 
money. According to information from Miami, one of the 
detainees, Rodolfo Frometa, admitted that they had attempted to 
carry out an expedition in Cuba, supposedly to land men ashore, 
but had problems with their boat. The report also points out 
that these members of Alpha 66 may be accused of violating the 
U.S. neutrality law. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

