<F P=100> Ecuador </F>
<H3> <TI>   Indians Announce Peaceful Protests for 8, 9 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0802161394 Quito Voz de los Andes in Spanish 2300 GMT 7 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0802161394 </F>
<F P=104>  Quito Voz de los Andes </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The Voz Andes" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Indian leaders announced that on 8 and 9 February, 
Ecuadoran Indians will stage peaceful demonstrations on the 
streets to protest the government decreed fuel increase. 
  Luis Macas, president of the Confederation of Indian 
Nationalities of Ecuador, said the people are currently asking 
the government to reconsider the law, which also interests the 
Indians. That is why we are going to stage a preventive 
demonstration. Macas pointed out that the Indians will stop 
their activities, set up blockades, and march during the day to 
express their dissatisfaction with the 71-percent fuel increase, 
which has been in effect for more than a week. 
  Macas added that if the government does not heed the 
Ecuadoran people's protests, they will obviously have to 
consider stronger measures. 

</TEXT>

