<F P=102>  PA0802143894 Managua Radio Nicaragua Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0802143894 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Nicaragua Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Monday, the Nicaraguan Government condemned the 
indiscriminate bombing of Sarajevo civilians and at the same 
time reiterated it categorically rejects the use of violence to 
settle differences in that strife-torn nation. In an official 
statement, the government of Violeta Barrios de Chamorro called 
on the warring sides in Bosnia-Herzegovina to talk so peace can 
return to that strife-torn region. Last Saturday, a 120-mm 
mortar shell killed 58 people and wounded another 142 at a 
Sarajevo market. 

