<H3> <TI>   * Swedish Program To Aid Small Businesses </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94P20345A </F>
<F P=103> 94P20345A </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:CSO 

  [Editorial Report] Managua LA PRENSA in Spanish of 25 
January 1994 on page 6 reports that the Swedish Association for 
International Development (ASDI) will invest $5.8 million 
starting in February to finance housing, community, and 
small-business programs in Leon, Chinandega, Ocotal, Somoto, and 
Esteli. The Local Development Program (Prodel) offices in those 
cities will be implemented by the ASDI programs. Small business 
owners will have to repay loans made for home and business 
improvements, according to the article. Prodel is also planning 
sewer and water projects as well as school and street 
improvements. 

</TEXT>

