<H3> <TI>   Physician Says Food Poisoning </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0802235694 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2100 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0802235694 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Itamar Franco spent the day at Alvorada 
Palace recovering from food poisoning caused by a chicken pie 
served during Sunday's dinner. The president has felt ill since 
yesterday. He has had a 38.5-degree-Celsius temperature and 
nausea. According to Carlos Alberto Farias, presidency of the 
Republic physician, the symptoms have already disappeared. The 
president has taken some medicines and is on a diet. 
  Dr. Farias said that President Franco will resume his 
activities tomorrow. He said: 
  [Begin recording] The president and his entourage had food 
poisoning resulting from food they ate during a dinner on Sunday 
night. The other guests had the same symptoms. He is currently 
recovering and will resume his normal activities tomorrow if he 
is feeling better. [end recording] 
  Dr. Farias said Franco had no sign of stress, as some 
newspapers have reported. 

</TEXT>

