<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Congress Approves Social Emergency Fund Bill </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY0802231794 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in 
Portuguese 2200 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY0802231794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] By 388 votes, Congress this evening approved the 
general text of the emergency social fund bill. Alexandre 
Garcia now reports live from the Congress plenary session. 
  [Begin Garcia recording] Despite a protest by the minority, 
the majority of lawmakers approved a request for an overall vote 
on all the individual topics on which separate voting had been 
requested. This means that a majority vote will defeat the 
requests for separate voting on individual topics, in order to 
let the original text of the bill -- which has already been 
approved -- remain unchanged. 
  Today's congressional agenda also includes a vote on the 
reduction of the presidential term from five to four years. [end 
recording] 
  We remind you that a second voting is due on the emergency 
social fund before it is published by the official gazette. 

</TEXT>

