<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gaviria To Be Investigated </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA0902030094 Paris AFP in Spanish 0143 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA0902030094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota, 8 Feb (AFP) -- The Council of 
State, Colombia's highest court of administrative litigation, on 
8 February asked the House of Representatives' investigative 
commission and the Attorney General's Office to investigate 
President Cesar Gaviria in connection with the presence of U.S. 
troops in the country. 
  The Council of State thinks Gaviria may have violated the 
Constitution by authorizing the presence of foreign soldiers in 
Colombian territory without consulting either the Council of 
State or the Senate. 

</TEXT>

